cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze gender associations in language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves clustering and labeling of semantic concepts, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of machine learning algorithms to infer gender associations and analyze language patterns also suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper draws from two different datasets, one of which is related to computer science professors, indicating the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
